eNCA's Manqoba Mchunu is there. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Police are trying to defuse a hostage situation at the International Pentecostal Holiness Church in Zuurbekom, west of Johannesburg. There is an apparent leadership dispute at the church. It's believed that there are close to 200 hostages. Several people have been injured and taken to hospital. Watch the video above for more on this developing story.